This paper is about open source python libraries for building conversational software, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions machine learning-based dialogue management, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The libraries also aim for ease of use, which is related to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also mentions minimal initial training data, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses testing extensively, which is related to cs.SD (Software Engineering).
